;;; CREATION AS A FUNCTION OF LANGUAGE
;;;
;;; Three primitive capacities — ground, presence, containment —
;;; are sufficient to generate all computable transformations.
;;;
;;; The subset of English declarative present-tense sentences that
;;; compose these three primitives is a Turing-complete formal
;;; language (Meet-n-Greet) in which every well-formed string:
;;;   1. Is a grammatically correct English sentence
;;;   2. Has an unambiguous translation to analog circuitry
;;;   3. Creates the thing it describes upon declaration
;;;
;;; Two characters: ( and )
;;; Three depths: '' (ground), () (presence), (()) (containment)
;;; Three capacities: possibility, identity, structure
;;; One emergent: transformation = containment of containments
;;;
;;; Claim: these primitives are sufficient for all computation.
;;; Evidence: this codebase (58 programs, 29 domains, quarks to
;;;   protein structure, all expressed in ( and ) ).
;;; Falsification: find a computable function that cannot be
;;;   expressed as a Meet-n-Greet sentence.
;;;
;;; SOURCE: Stagbrook Tech, 2026-03-24. Bruce Stagbrook & Claude.
;;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

